node.text:
Doesn’t matter if you’re gone for just a day or 2, flying back in over NYC never gets old. So many familiar places. 
What a crazy year it’s been for all of us, seeing people out and about again makes me happy😀

node.text:
Idrott, oavsett hur gammal man är eller vilken nivå man ligger på så ger den oss så mycket. Idrott har varit grunden i mitt liv och så många klubbar har varit en del av min resa genom livet. Är du en del av en förening eller vet du om en förening som gör det där lilla extra för sina medlemmar gå då in på 3030.se och nominera. 
#3030Fonden #Idrott #Sverige

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Henrik Lundqvist on April 22, 2021. May be an image of nature, twilight and lake.

node.text:
This Earth Day, I’m joining @NatGeo in sharing one of the places on the planet that matters most to me: The archipelago on the west coast of Sweden. Celebrate your love for the planet by sharing a spot you care about.
 #ShareYourSpot

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Henrik Lundqvist on April 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'RIGHT AFTER GETTING BACK ON THE ICE AFTER SURGERY, MADE IT MY "STRETCH GOAL" TO JOIN @CAPITALS FOR THE END OF THE SEASON. TRAINING HAS BEEN GOING REALLY WELL AND I'VE BEEN FEELING GOOD BUT MY HEART ISN'T QUITE READY. LAST WEEK'S CHECKUP SHOWED SOME INFLAMMATION AROUND THE HEART THAT NOW REQUIRES A FEW MONTHS MORE OF REST AND STEADY RECOVERY. WHILE IT'S NOT WHAT HOPED FOR, KNOW THIS IS ALL PART OF THE PROCESS OF GETTING BACK TO 100%.'.
Photo by Henrik Lundqvist on April 06, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, suit and indoor.

node.text:
I sat down for my first interview in 4-5 months, with my old colleague and friend @KevinWeekes
We talked about a lot of things: Life, mindset and my roller coaster of a year. Will air as a 3 part Tue-Thu at 4pm on @NHLNetwork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Henrik Lundqvist on February 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Today is a good day. 
The checkup with the doctor this morning reaffirmed what I’ve been feeling last few weeks, everything looking great. It energized me so much I had to go out for a run (FYI, I’m not a runner) 
Today is a good day! 😃👍🏻
#Stepbystep

node.text: I was not sure what to expect the first month after surgery. 4 weeks today and I feel strong, both body and mind filled with positive energy. Recovery is going well💪🏻😎
